\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 # ACTIVE SPEC: Phase 14.1 \'97 Native App Shell Layout Refactor\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## Overview\cb1 \
\cb3 **Phase:** 14.1 \'97 Layout / UX Enhancement  \cb1 \
\cb3 **Priority:** High  \cb1 \
\cb3 **Target:** Transition the ARM sports management app from a "document-style" scrolling layout to a "Native App Shell" feel  \cb1 \
\cb3 **Status:** Ready for Implementation  \cb1 \
\cb3 **Previous Phase:** 13 Complete (PDF Export Feature)\cb1 \
\
\cb3 **Use this template to generate feature specifications that follow the strict Tech Lead/Developer workflow defined in `.clinerules`.**\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## When to Use This Template\cb1 \
\cb3 - For any new feature or significant enhancement\cb1 \
\cb3 - When you need to create an `ACTIVE_SPEC.md` for the Developer (Claude)\cb1 \
\cb3 - Before handing any task to the Developer for implementation\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## How to Use This Template\cb1 \
\cb3 1. Fill in all bracketed `[ ]` sections with specific details\cb1 \
\cb3 2. Keep the total spec under 500 words (prioritize clarity over brevity)\cb1 \
\cb3 3. Ensure all architectural decisions are locked upfront\cb1 \
\cb3 4. Provide exact code snippets for UI implementation\cb1 \
\cb3 5. Make the spec self-contained - Developer should not need to read other docs\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## \uc0\u55356 \u57263  Why (1-2 sentences)\cb1 \
\cb3 Transition the ARM sports management app from a "document-style" scrolling layout to a "Native App Shell" feel where specific containers scroll internally while the viewport remains fixed. This improves mobile UX by preventing scroll-chaining, ensuring sticky headers work correctly, and creating a more native app experience.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## \uc0\u55356 \u57303 \u65039  Architecture Decisions (Locked)\cb1 \
\cb3 1. **Fixed Viewport Strategy** - Use `100dvh` (dynamic viewport height) instead of `100vh` to handle mobile Safari address bar\cb1 \
\cb3 2. **Internal Scroll Containers** - Main content areas (Roster, Master Grid, Starters) must use `overflow-y: auto` with `overscroll-behavior: contain`\cb1 \
\cb3 3. **Sticky Headers** - Master Availability Grid headers must remain `position: sticky` with proper z-index stacking\cb1 \
\cb3 4. **Tailwind CSS Implementation** - Convert inline styles to Tailwind CSS classes for consistency\cb1 \
\cb3 5. **Mobile-First Approach** - All solutions must work on iOS Safari with address bar and Android Chrome\cb1 \
\cb3 6. **No Breaking Changes** - Maintain existing functionality while improving layout structure\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## \uc0\u55357 \u56513  Files to Touch (Exact paths + what to do)\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ### Updated Files:\cb1 \
\cb3 1. **`src/components/Layout.tsx`** - Refactor to use fixed viewport with `100dvh` and proper scroll container structure\cb1 \
\cb3 2. **`src/pages/Grid.tsx`** - Enhance sticky table headers with proper Tailwind CSS and ensure they work within the new scroll container\cb1 \
\cb3 3. **`src/pages/Roster.tsx`** - Convert inline styles to Tailwind CSS and ensure proper scroll container behavior\cb1 \
\cb3 4. **`src/index.css`** - Add global CSS utilities for scroll behavior and viewport handling if needed\cb1 \
\cb3 5. **`src/pages/Board.tsx`** - Ensure Selection Board works within new scroll container structure\cb1 \
\cb3 6. **`src/pages/DepthChart.tsx`** - Ensure Depth Chart works within new scroll container structure\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ### Integration Points:\cb1 \
\cb3 7. **All page components** - Must work within the new Layout container structure without breaking existing functionality\cb1 \
\cb3 8. **Modal/dialog components** - Must prevent scroll-chaining when open (overscroll-behavior)\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## \uc0\u55356 \u57256  UI Implementation (Exact Tailwind/JSX - copy-paste ready)\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ### Layout.tsx Refactor:\cb1 \
\cb3 ```tsx\cb1 \
